		<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
	
			<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
			Been camping IG Dip in King room a lot lately with my <BR>
guild buddy and we have been getting at least 2 or 3 <BR>
of these per night in a few hours of camping giant.  The<BR>
High Priest may spawn instead of Patriarch, but I don't <BR>
think it's that rare.  He seems to pop every 90 minutes <BR>
and always has the coronet.  I personally have had trouble<BR>
finding buyers so lately I've either given them to newbies<BR>
who complete &quot;mini quests&quot; I design for them or I give them<BR>
to guildmates.  Not that I'm wasteful, just that I hate carting<BR>
stuff like this around with me auctioning it off hoping someone<BR>
low enough to want it has the money to buy it.  More trouble<BR>
than it's worth, and I hate the auctions.  <BR>
<BR>
Anyway, I agree this is a very nice headpiece for midlevels, <BR>
especially druids who get robbed in the types of armor they can<BR>
wear.  I have a tip for lower levels who want are looking for <BR>
king room lore stuff.  Perma is almost never camped heavily. Me <BR>
and my partner routinely are there all evening and see two or maybe<BR>
three others in the whole zone.  After an hour or two chances are<BR>
we both have some of the more common lore items (frost totems, etc) <BR>
and are unable to loot anymore.  Any brave newbies who invised in <BR>
and /shouted what they were hoping to loot would probably find us<BR>
more than willing to /shout back when the stuff is available to be <BR>
picked up.  We've done this with frost totems many times (for crafted<BR>
armor quest).  Now getting to the King Room to loot the dead mob will <BR>
be risky I know, but if you can invis yourself and don't mind a risk, <BR>
this might be a good way to get some goodies. <BR>
<BR>
Cass<BR>
47 Ench<BR>
M Marr
